---
import MainLayout from '@/layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Review the terms and conditions that apply when you use Global Events Travels services and website."
>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-secondary-600 to-secondary-500 py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container-custom text-center text-white">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/80 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Please read these terms carefully before using our website or booking a trek, tour, or yatra with us.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none">
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
          Last updated: {new Date().getFullYear()}
        </p>

        <p>
          These Terms of Service (&quot;Terms&quot;) govern your use of the website
          <strong>globaleventstravels.com</strong> and any services provided by
          <strong> Global Events Travels </strong>(&quot;we&quot;, &quot;us&quot;, or &quot;our&quot;).
          By accessing our website or making a booking, you agree to be bound by these Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Eligibility</h2>
        <p>
          By using our services, you confirm that you are at least 18 years old or have the consent of
          a parent or legal guardian, and that you are legally capable of entering into a binding contract.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Bookings &amp; Payments</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>All bookings are subject to availability and confirmation from our team.</li>
          <li>Prices, inclusions, and exclusions are specified on the respective trek or package pages.</li>
          <li>
            Payment terms (advance amount, balance due date, and accepted payment methods) will be shared
            at the time of booking.
          </li>
          <li>
            Your booking is considered confirmed only after we receive the specified advance payment and
            you receive a written confirmation from us.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Cancellations &amp; Refunds</h2>
        <p>
          Our general cancellation and refund rules are outlined on our
          <a href="/cancellation-refund" class="text-primary-600 underline">Cancellation &amp; Refund</a>
          page. Specific trip-level terms (if any) shared at the time of booking will override the general policy.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Participant Responsibilities</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide accurate personal and medical information at the time of booking.</li>
          <li>
            Follow all instructions given by trek leaders, guides, and support staff for your safety and
            the safety of the group.
          </li>
          <li>
            Maintain basic fitness levels appropriate for the selected trek or activity and inform us of any
            medical conditions in advance.
          </li>
          <li>
            Respect local communities, culture, environment, and &quot;leave no trace&quot; principles.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Itinerary Changes &amp; Force Majeure</h2>
        <p>
          Mountains and outdoor environments are unpredictable. We may modify itineraries, routes, or schedules
          due to weather conditions, natural disasters, political situations, local regulations, or any other
          circumstances beyond our control.
        </p>
        <p>
          In such cases, we will make reasonable efforts to provide an equivalent alternative. Refunds or
          compensation in force majeure situations will be handled as per our policies and at our discretion.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          While we take all reasonable precautions for your safety, trekking and adventure activities carry
          inherent risks. By participating, you acknowledge and accept these risks.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            We are not liable for any loss, injury, damage, or expense arising from events beyond our reasonable control.
          </li>
          <li>
            You are responsible for your personal belongings, travel insurance, and any medical expenses incurred.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Travel Insurance</h2>
        <p>
          We strongly recommend that all participants obtain comprehensive travel insurance that covers
          high-altitude trekking, medical emergencies, evacuation, and trip cancellations.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          All content on this website, including text, images, logos, and designs, is the property of
          Global Events Travels or its content providers and is protected by applicable copyright and
          intellectual property laws. You may not copy, reproduce, or distribute any content without our
          prior written permission.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Prohibited Uses</h2>
        <p>You agree not to use our website or services to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Engage in any unlawful, harmful, or fraudulent activity</li>
          <li>Upload or share malicious code, spam, or offensive content</li>
          <li>Infringe upon the rights of others, including privacy and intellectual property rights</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. The latest version will always be available on this page.
          Continued use of our website or services after updates constitutes your acceptance of the revised Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us at
          <a href="mailto:info@globaleventstravels.com" class="text-primary-600 underline">
            info@globaleventstravels.com
          </a>.
        </p>

        <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 mt-8">
          This page is a general template and does not constitute legal advice. Please consult with a legal
          professional to review and tailor these Terms for your specific business and jurisdiction.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

